<title>FRANCE: Degremont in Botswana water supply deal.</title>
<headline>Degremont in Botswana water supply deal.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-01-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lyonnaise des Eaux unit Degremont said on Monday it had won part of a contract worth a total 240 million francs to supply drinking water in Botswana.</p>
<p>The contract, awarded to a consortium which also includes Anglo-American firm LTA, and put together with Japanese backing, is for three treatment plants to supply the capital Gaborone and the south of the country, Degremont said in a statement.</p>
<p>Construction is provisionally due to take 28 months.  </p>
<p>&quot;The total value of the contract, awarded to a consortium which includes LTA and has Japanese financing, is 240 million francs including public works,&quot; Degremont said.</p>
<p>A spokeswoman declined to give Degremont's share in the total amount of the contract.</p>
<p>-- Paris newsroom +331 4221 5452</p>
